FBIS4-28199 "dreas111_i_94001" FBIS-EAS-94-111 Daily Report 8 Jun 1994 Cambodia Pol Pot's `Serious Brain Illness' Reported Pol Pot's `Serious Brain Illness' Reported Government Spokesman Announces OW0806145894 Tokyo KYODO in English 1440 GMT 8 Jun 94 OW0806145894 Tokyo KYODO English BFN [Text] Phnom Penh, June 8 KYODO -- Khmer Rouge leader Pol Pot has a serious brain illness, a Cambodian Government spokesman said Wednesday [8 June]. The spokesman did not identify his source of information. Another senior government official told Kyodo News Service that he has not confirmed the report. Pol Pot, held responsible for the deaths of hundreds of thousands of Cambodians under the Khmer Rouge regime in the late 1970s, disappeared from public in the early 1980s. He is reportedly hiding in the Thai-Cambodian border area and escaped from the Khmer Rouge's capital town of Pailin during a Cambodian Government offensive on the rebels' headquarters in March.
